# gen211, Italian probe: teach a new ask_name surface form through the Italian trigger
# ("impara \"…\" come chiedere il mio nome"). The same KB-first mechanism, two languages,
# one code path — the bilingual ratchet. `norm` is the canonicalized surface (mio->my),
# so the handler matches the canonical form; teach-time and match-time share the same
# transform, so a taught Italian form recalls the name like any other.
> mi chiamo Bob
< Nice to meet you, Bob!
> impara "come mi chiami" come chiedere il mio nome
< Got it - I'll take "come mi chiami" as a way to ask your name now.
> come mi chiami
< Your name is Bob.
